  "texts": [
    "Building on those definitional ambiguities, provisions emphasize metaphorical definition of \"virality\" instead of granular technical factors like source credibility, frequency, recency, and message exposure that psychologically enable belief formation (Articles 26, 27) [78].Uneven Obligations Differentiated responsibilities across online intermediaries covered under due diligence provisions (Code: DD) in Articles 10-15, 35-37 do not sufficiently account for varying capacities and risks of enabling harms, disregarding potential anti-competitive impacts that contradict intended proportionality.",
    "As denounced by [107], VLOPs might be able to 'capture' and influence their mandatory auditors.",
    "As remarked, VLOPs must undergo yearly independent audits (Code: AD), yet because there are limited platforms that meet the VLOP threshold, these platforms might dominate the demand for audits.",
    "Auditors may then feel pressure to avoid overly scrutinizing VLOPs in order to retain their business, creating a 'go-to' choices of auditors for big platforms.",
    "The ratio of increasing platform user threshold and heightened obligations might overlook risks from smaller platforms [107]."
